# 🎯 COMPLETE BUILD INSTRUCTIONS

## Step 1: Create All Files

```bash
mkdir sukaina-chat && cd sukaina-chat
mkdir -p cmd internal/{models,database,auth,handlers,websocket}

# Create each file with content above
```

## Step 2: Install Dependencies

```bash
go mod tidy
```

## Step 3: Run Locally

```bash
# Start database
docker-compose up postgres -d

# Run app
go run cmd/main.go
```

## Step 4: Test

```bash
# Health check
curl http://localhost:8080/health

# Register
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"username":"alice","email":"alice@test.com","password":"pass123"}'

# Login
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/auth/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"username":"alice","password":"pass123"}'
```

## Step 5: Deploy to Railway

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Sukaina Chat complete"
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/sukaina-chat.git
git push -u origin main

# Then connect on railway.app
```

